Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle with the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g}, sliced pepper and onion and fry until just soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Continue to stir while it cooks.

Stir the @tomato puree{30%g} into the veg. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @hot sauce{30%g}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{100%ml} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix to combine.

Bring to the boil, then simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board. Cut into 1cm chunks.

In a #small bowl{}, squeeze in half the lime juice. Add the avocado and stir to combine.

When the beans are ready, stir in the lime zest.

Slice the remaining lime into wedges.

Once the wedges are ready, divide between your bowls. Spoon over the chorizo, beans and remaining sauce in the pan - wedges loaded!

Top with the avocado chunks and crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g}.

Drizzle over the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} to finish. Serve with a lime wedge on the side.

Enjoy!